This article is a presidential memorandum from August 17, 2010, regarding the designation of officials to act as the Director of the Court Services and Offender Supervision Agency for the District of Columbia. The memorandum outlines the order of succession for officials to assume the role of Director in case the current Director is unable to perform their duties. It also includes exceptions and states that the President has the discretion to depart from this memorandum when designating an acting Director. The purpose of the memorandum is to improve the internal management of the executive branch.